OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1782434875
OL,3,CMahmood in standoff with No 10 after
OL,4,Ccall to sack junior minister
OL,6,FLabour's ruling body confirmed the
OL,7,Ftimetable for electing a new party
OL,8,Fleader, which will likely see Mr
OL,9,FBurnham installed on July 17.
OL,11,FPotential candidates have from July 9
OL,12,Fto July 15 to amass the backing of the
OL,13,F81 MPs required, and until July 16 to
OL,14,Fgather nominations from affiliated
OL,15,Fgroups such as trade unions.
OL,17,FIf no challenger emerges with the
OL,18,Fbacking of the 81 MPs required, then a
OL,19,Fconference will be held on July 17
OL,20,Fwhere Mr Burnham will likely be
OL,21,Fannounced as winner.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
